### Base URL
GET http://localhost:5000/

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### Authentication Ping
http://localhost:5000/api/_authping


### Authentication ping with header owner: alice
GET http://localhost:5000/api/_authping
Authorization: Bearer dev-alice

### Authentication ping with header owner: bob
GET http://localhost:5000/api/_authping
Authorization: Bearer dev-bob

###
http://localhost:5000
X-Correlation-Id: my-trace-1


###############################################################################
# Properties (WP03)
# All endpoints require authentication; cross-owner access returns 404.
###############################################################################

@alice = dev-alice
@bob   = dev-bob

### Create a property as Alice
# @name createProperty
POST http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Main House"
}

### List Alice's properties (uses last create above for context)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Get one property by id (replace <id> with the id from the create response)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/properties/{{createProperty.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Rename the property
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/properties/{{createProperty.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Main Residence"
}

### Bob tries to read Alice's property -> 404 (not 403, no leak)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/properties/{{createProperty.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{bob}}

### Anonymous create -> 401 problem+json
POST http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Should be rejected"
}

### Validation: empty name -> 400
POST http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": ""
}


###############################################################################
# Jobs (WP05)
# Owns the lifecycle: create -> tick steps -> complete. Step mutation
# beyond initial creation is WP07 and not represented here.
###############################################################################

### Step 0: ensure Alice has a property to host the job (sets createProperty
###         again so the rest of the file can chain off it; harmless re-run).
# @name createProperty
POST http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Main House"
}

### Create a Job under that property with three steps
# @name createJob
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "{{createProperty.response.body.id}}",
  "name": "Service boiler",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-01",
  "steps": [
    { "description": "Shut off gas" },
    { "description": "Drain system" },
    { "description": "Replace filter" }
  ]
}

### List all of Alice's jobs
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### List jobs filtered by property
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs?propertyId={{createProperty.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### List only Active jobs
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs?status=Active
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Get the job by id (includes embedded steps)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Tick step 1
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/steps/{{createJob.response.body.steps[0].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Tick step 2
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/steps/{{createJob.response.body.steps[1].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Try to complete the job - expect 400 steps_incomplete (one step still unticked)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Tick the last step
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/steps/{{createJob.response.body.steps[2].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Complete the job - now succeeds (200, status flips to Completed)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Try to tick again on the completed job -> 400 job_completed
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/steps/{{createJob.response.body.steps[0].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Untick attempt on completed job -> 400 job_completed
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/steps/{{createJob.response.body.steps[0].id}}/untick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Complete an already-completed job -> 400 job_already_completed
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Bob tries to read Alice's job -> 404 (no leak)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{createJob.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{bob}}

### Anonymous create -> 401 problem+json
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "{{createProperty.response.body.id}}",
  "name": "Should be rejected",
  "steps": []
}

### Validation: empty name -> 400
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "{{createProperty.response.body.id}}",
  "name": "",
  "steps": []
}

### Validation: cross-owner property id -> 404 (no leak)
###   Run this AFTER signing in as Bob to a fresh property elsewhere if you
###   want a real cross-owner check; the simple shape below uses an
###   intentionally bogus id so the API treats it as not-found.
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "non-existent-id",
  "name": "Hijack attempt",
  "steps": []
}


###############################################################################
# Step mutation + Job rename / due-date (WP07)
# Builds on the createProperty + createJob named requests above. Run the
# Properties + Jobs blocks first so {{createJob.response.body.id}} resolves.
###############################################################################

### Reset state: create a fresh property + job for the WP07 block
# @name wp07Property
POST http://localhost:5000/api/properties
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "WP07 House"
}

# @name wp07Job
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "propertyId": "{{wp07Property.response.body.id}}",
  "name": "Service boiler",
  "dueDate": "2026-06-01",
  "steps": [
    { "description": "Shut off gas" },
    { "description": "Drain system" },
    { "description": "Replace filter" }
  ]
}

### Add a step at the end of the checklist
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Refill expansion tank"
}

### Add step: empty description -> 400 validation
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": ""
}

### Edit a step's description (uses the FIRST step from job create)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Shut off gas at the meter"
}

### Edit step: over 500 chars -> 400
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": ""
}

### Reorder: reverse the step list
###   Body lists all step ids in the desired new order. Server renumbers
###   Order to 0..N-1.
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/order
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedStepIds": [
    "{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[2].id}}",
    "{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[1].id}}",
    "{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}"
  ]
}

### Reorder: partial list -> 400 validation
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/order
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedStepIds": ["{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}"]
}

### Remove the LAST step
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[2].id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Remove: unknown id -> 404
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/no-such-step
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Rename the job (PATCH /api/jobs/{id} with just `name`)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Annual boiler service"
}

### Update the due date (PATCH with just `dueDate`)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": "2026-12-31"
}

### Clear the due date (explicit null, not omitted)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dueDate": null
}

### Rename + reschedule in one call
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Spring boiler service",
  "dueDate": "2027-03-15"
}

### PATCH /api/jobs/{id} with empty body -> 400 (no fields to change)
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
}

### Rename the property (PATCH /api/properties/{id})
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/properties/{{wp07Property.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "WP07 House (renamed)"
}

### Tick all remaining steps, then test sealing matrix
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

###
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[1].id}}/tick
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Complete the job
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Sealing matrix: add step on completed job -> 400 job_completed
POST http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Should be rejected"
}

### Sealing matrix: remove step on completed job -> 400 job_completed
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}

### Sealing matrix: edit step on completed job -> 400 job_completed
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Should be rejected"
}

### Sealing matrix: reorder on completed job -> 400 job_completed
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}/steps/order
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedStepIds": [
    "{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[1].id}}",
    "{{wp07Job.response.body.steps[0].id}}"
  ]
}

### Sealing matrix: PATCH job on completed job -> 400 job_completed
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/jobs/{{wp07Job.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{alice}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Should be rejected"
}